{
  "texts": [
    "This can also be an issue with personal data, privacy, and informed consent, including GDPR considerations.",
    "There have been cases of individual data being used without consent (c.f.",
    "De Vynck, 2023).",
    "It is the researcher's responsibility to comply with legal restrictions on their use of data and to make research participants aware that their data is being used by a combination of human and computer tools.",
    "In general, these two ethical and legal issues go against the tenets of open science and the principles of the scientific method, but this is a larger issue when mixing profit-oriented agendas with those of research."
  ]
}